<br>
----------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I tested Fury of the gods with 46 battlechant on pendragon. Basically they stack better, I was getting an average of 35 from battlechant and 40 from the ra when stacked. I was killing blue and yellow mobs in DF. <br>
<br>
It's still a worthless RA even if it was 10 pts. Maybe if it was 6 pts (double the cost of the rain damage add ra's) then I might consider it.<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Little fury of the Gods:<br>
<br>
In an average rvr group you have about 3-5 melee types. So each one probably averages 6 swings in a 30 second period. At a rate of 40 per hit, each melee does 240 more damage over a 30 second period with the little fury on. <br>
<br>
So a group with 5 melee types in it, over a 30 second period, will do 1200 more damage with &quot;Little Fury&quot; ra being used. Of course if any in the group are mez, rooted, stunned, snared, it greatly reduces the damage output.<br>
<br>
